# Cursor AI rules for Tarnish Jira Fork

## Project Context
- 2,651 Java/Kotlin source files, 30K+ JSON data files
- JDK 21 for server, JDK 11 for client
- Gradle multi-module: game-server, game-client
- Always read AGENTS.md first for project map

## Key Docs (read in order)
1. AGENTS.md — project structure map
2. docs/game-scope.md — what's in the game
3. docs/test-plan.md — offline test strategy
4. docs/workflows/ — how-to recipes for common tasks
5. prompts/README.md — 24 audit/dev prompts
6. code_index.json — instant file lookup

## File Discovery
- USE code_index.json BEFORE grepping — it maps every source file to class name
- Check AGENTS.md for common path patterns (commands, skills, shops, NPCs)
- 30K+ data files in game-server/data/ are mostly cache; grep there only as last resort
- For security audit: prompts/03-security/
- For data validation: prompts/02-data-audit/

## Code Style
- Java for core engine (com.osroyale package)
- Kotlin for plugins (game-server/plugins/)
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new modules
- Content goes in plugins or content/ directory, not new top-level packages
- Data definitions go in JSON files under game-server/data/def/

## Building
- Windows: `.\gradlew.bat :game-server:classes` — compile server
- WSL: `./gradlew :game-server:classes`
- Windows: `.\gradlew.bat :game-server:test` — run tests
- WSL: `./gradlew :game-server:test`
- Server port: 43594

## Common Tasks
- Add command: game-server/plugins/plugin/command/<Rank>CommandPlugin.java → see docs/workflows/commands.md
- Add item click: game-server/plugins/plugin/click/item/ → see docs/workflows/plugins.md
- Add skill: game-server/src/main/java/com/osroyale/content/skill/impl/ → see docs/workflows/skills.md
- Add shop: game-server/data/def/store/stores.json + content/store/ → see docs/workflows/shops.md
- Add NPC spawn: game-server/data/def/npc/npc_spawns.json → see docs/workflows/npcs.md
- Add NPC drops: game-server/data/def/npc/npc_drops.json → see docs/workflows/npcs.md
- Add item: game-server/data/def/item/item_definitions.json → see docs/workflows/items.md
- Add equipment: game-server/data/def/equipment/equipment_definitions.json → see docs/workflows/items.md

## Client-Server Boundary
- Server-only: JSON data, plugins, skills, combat formulas
- Needs client: new item models (ID > ~7K), new packet opcodes, new interfaces
- Full guide: prompts/00-cross-cutting/client-server-boundary.md
